          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 58</h1><p><strong>Questions 11 - 16</strong></p><p>For each question, choose <strong>TWO</strong> letters (from <strong>A - E</strong>) and write them in any order in answer boxes.</p><p>According to the guide, which TWO facts are true of the history of the museum?</p><p>11</p><p>12</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    It was opened in 1974.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    It is a museum for children.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    You can learn about a specific period of national history there.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong>    It is expensive to run and maintain.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong>    A university in the area plays an important role in its running.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Which TWO facts are true of the original town?</p><p>13</p><p>14</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Its name came from a geographical feature.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    It was at the same location as the museum.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Its most successful period came several centuries after it was built.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong>    It was built by monks.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong>    More people live there now than lived there 500 years ago.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Which TWO facts are true of the museum today?</p><p>15</p><p>16</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    It is smaller than the original settlement.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    It contains more houses than the original settlement.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    It is the biggest museum of its type in the country.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong>    It shows medieval life better than any other museum.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong>    Many of the buildings were taken from the original village.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
